HEADWORD: Rhodophane
<hw>Rho"do*phane</hw> <pr>(r⟦omac⟧"d⟦osl⟧*f⟦amac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>"ro`don</grk> the rose + <grk>fai`nein</grk> to
show.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The red pigment contained in the
inner segments of the cones of the retina in animals. See
<er>Chromophane</er>.</def> <rj><au>W. K⟦uum⟧hne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
